  "prompt": "What are the main reasons why students from Boston University don't graduate on time?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why students from Boston University, or any university, may not graduate on time. Common factors include:\n\n1. **Academic Challenges**: Students might struggle with the coursework, leading to a need for extra time to complete their degrees. This can include difficulties in particular subjects or overall academic performance.\n\n2. **Changing Majors**: Many students change their major during their time at university, which can extend their time in school. Transitioning to a new program may require them to take additional courses that were not part of their initial plan.\n\n3. **Personal Issues**: Life events, such as health problems, family responsibilities, or personal crises, can impact a student\u2019s ability to focus on their studies and complete their degree on time.\n\n4. **Financial Constraints**: Economic factors, such as the need to work part-time or full-time while studying, can delay graduation as students may need to take fewer credits per semester or take breaks from their studies.\n\n5. **Course Availability**: Sometimes, required courses may not be offered every semester, or there may be scheduling conflicts, causing students to delay fulfilling their degree requirements.\n\n6. **Extracurricular Commitments**: Engaging in extensive extracurricular activities, internships, or jobs that require significant time commitments can divert attention from academics.\n\n7. **Social Integration**: Some students may struggle to integrate socially, which can affect their mental well-being and engagement with their studies, leading to delays.\n\n8. **Advising and Support**: Inadequate academic advising or a lack of support services may lead to poor course selection or unawareness of degree requirements, resulting in longer completion times.\n\nAddressing these issues often involves enhancing academic support services, providing better financial aid options, and improving course availability and scheduling.",
